China Stocks: Maanshan Steel, Phenix Optical, UFIDA Software

-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 
2011-08-19T07:22:42Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-19/china-stocks-maanshan-steel-phenix-optical-ufida-software.html
Shares of the following companies
had unusual moves in  China  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the 3 p.m. close.  The Shanghai Composite Index, which tracks the bigger of
China’s stock exchanges, fell 1 percent to 2,534.36. The  CSI 300
Index (SHSZ300)  lost 0.9 percent to 2,807.66.  Maanshan Iron & Steel (600808)  Co. (600808 CH), China’s fourth-
largest listed steelmaker, dropped 1.6 percent to 2.99 yuan, the
most since Aug. 8. The company’s first-half profit fell 70
percent to 310 million yuan ($48 million) because of higher raw
material costs, according to a statement to the Shanghai Stock
Exchange.  Phenix Optical Co. (600071 CH) sank 4.3 percent to 10.21,
its biggest decline since Aug. 8. The company’s first-half net
income dropped 91 percent to 2.8 million yuan from a year
earlier, according to a statement to the Shanghai Stock
Exchange.  UFIDA Software Co. (600588 CH) added 3.6 percent to 23.70
yuan, its biggest gain since July 7. The company’s first-half
net income may have risen more than 320 percent from 26.5
million yuan a year earlier, according to a statement to the
 Shanghai Stock Exchange .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Darren Boey at 
 dboey@bloomberg.net  